🚀 CPI Index System – Refined UI & Workflow Specification
________________________________________
🔹 1. Upload Section (Data Intake)
✅ Pre-Upload Validation
Before enabling upload:
1.	Month & Year Validation
o	Validate file metadata against selected filters (Month, Year).
o	❌ If mismatch → show error:
	“Selected period does not match file data.”
2.	File Count & Schema Validation
o	Compare:
	Number of uploaded files
	Column names vs definition fields (master config)
o	❌ If mismatch:
	Show:
	Missing columns
	Extra columns
	Missing files
3.	Support Downloads
o	📥 Download:
	Error log file (CSV/TXT)
	Sample ZIP file (correct format template)
________________________________________
✅ Upload Flow (UI Behavior)
•	If validation passes:
o	Enable Upload ZIP button
•	On clicking Upload:
o	Hide upload form
o	Show:
	Upload progress bar
	Status logs (streaming if possible)
•	After Upload:
o	❌ If failed:
	Show error summary
	Show upload section again
o	✅ If success:
	Show:
	Upload summary
	Start Compilation Process
________________________________________
🔹 2. Compilation Section
⚙️ Compilation Logic
•	Use:
o	Previous indices from DB (for imputation)
o	Master data from DB (not static files)
•	Store:
o	Raw uploaded data
o	Cleaned/validated data
o	Compilation outputs
________________________________________
📊 Compilation UI States
🟡 In Progress
•	Show:
o	Progress %
o	Logs
o	Steps (validation → processing → indexing)
🔴 Failed
•	Show:
o	Error summary
o	Download error logs
🟢 Success
•	Show:
o	Compilation Summary
o	Status: SUCCESS
o	Enable button:
👉 “Import to DB”
________________________________________
🔹 3. Import to Database
•	Enabled only after successful compilation
After Import:
•	Store:
o	Final indices
o	Price data
o	Outputs
•	Show:
o	Import summary
o	Record counts
o	Time taken
________________________________________
🔹 4. Role-Based Visibility
Stage	Access
Before Finalization	Compiler + Approver
After Finalization	All Users
________________________________________
🔹 5. Filter Section (Smart Defaults)
🎯 Auto Selection Logic
•	Based on current date:
o	M-1 → Provisional
o	M-2 → Final
________________________________________
📅 Compilation Rules
•	Reference Date: 12th of every month
Condition	Rule
Date < 12	Compilation allowed
Date ≥ 12	Compilation blocked
________________________________________
🔓 Override Logic (Approver/Admin)
For Final Data:
•	Approver can:
o	Reset final compilation
o	Re-run compilation
Release Control:
•	Approver can:
o	Mark index as Finalized
o	Release for public access
Admin Privileges:
•	Can:
o	Re-open frozen compilation
o	Allow re-compilation anytime
